      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks for that. i think i get the ratio part, but can you expand more on the actual physical sensation? like, when the frequencies are that close together and clashing, what's happening at the level of the cochlea or the auditory nerve? i've heard something about \"beats\" or interference patterns making it feel harsh or rough. can you explain that part?",
